main event: The witness observed a round, hazy object in the sky that remained stationary for several minutes before fading from view.
interesting points: The object did not seem to be powered or propelled, as it did not move in a manner indicating it was powered.
The object did not blink or show any lights.
The object was estimated to be about 15 miles away and at an elevation of around 60 degrees.
Other witnesses may have also observed the object, but their identities have been redacted.
photographs: yes, but not provided in the image
